         <div type="translation" ana="b1" xml:id="zoor0346.translation" corresp="#zoor0346.transcription">
            <p>One (is) the God, the Lord of all. Monument of Kyra, (daughter) of Elias, who lived
               18 years having a good name, and died on (the) 1st (day) of the month Artemisios, in
               (the) 13th indiction, in (the) year 430. Be of good cheer, no one (is) immortal.</p>
         </div>
      </body>
      <back>
         <div type="commentary" ana="b2">
            <p>The inscription gives the date as the 1st day of the month Artemisios, in the 13th
               indiction, in the year 430 according to the Era of the Province of Arabia, that is
               April 21, 535 CE. The tombstone is one of about 700 discovered in Byzantine Zoora.
               The majority of the Greek tombstones from this location have been identified as
               Christian.</p>
         </div>
